True Video Uniqueizer

This script uniqueizes your videos.
It will be useful if you need to change the videos.
This script is using ffmpeg to convert your videos.

- Random filename option
- Flip option
- Clear metadata option
- Trim start option
- Random resolution
- Random volume
- Random gamma
- Random saturation
- Random brightness
- Random speed
- Random crop


Instruction:
- (Optional) Set mode inside "convert.bat" file (easy, normal, hard, super_hard, ultra_hard, custom), for example: SET MODE=hard
- (Optional) Set random filename inside "convert.bat" file, for example: SET RAND_FILENAME=1
- (Optional) Set flip inside "convert.bat" file, for example: SET FLIP=-vf hflip
- (Optional) Set clear metadata inside "convert.bat" file, for example: SET CLEAR_METADATA=-map_metadata -1
- (Optional) Set trim start inside "convert.bat" file, for example: SET TRIM_START="1"
- (Optional) Set custom mode params (if MODE=custom selected)
- Place one or many videos inside "input" folder
- Run the "convert.bat" script
- The result will be inside the "output" folder

Custom mode params:
To set custom mode: "SET MODE=custom"
And change custom params:
IF %MODE%==custom (
    SET RAND_FILENAME=0
    SET FLIP=
    SET CLEAR_METADATA=-map_metadata -1
    SET TRIM_START="1"
    SET RAND_RESOLUTION="1.10"
    SET RAND_VOLUME="1.20"
    SET RAND_GAMMA="1.20"
    SET RAND_SATURATION="1.20"
    SET RAND_BRIGHTNESS="0.20"
    SET RAND_SPEED="1.08"
    SET RAND_CROP="0.90"
)
You may share your config with each other.
For example, you made a config that was successful on TikTok (YouTube Shorts, Instagram), then you may share it with other members.

System Requirements:
- Windows OS (7, 8, 10, 11)
